# Note Skill

Use the managed weeknotes handler for journal entries.

## Input Contract

User input is everything after `/note`.

- `add <text...>`: append a timestamped note to the Journal section.
- `find <text...>`: search current note context for matching text.

## Execution Rules

Always execute exactly one command:

```bash
/home/node/.openclaw/skills/{{ openclaw_weeknotes_skill_name }}/handler.sh note <raw-user-input>
```

If the user asks natural-language memory questions about today/recent activity
(for example "Did I ... today?" / "Habe ich heute ...?"), run:

`note find <concise search phrase>`

before answering. Use handler output as source of truth.

When no input is provided, return:

`Usage: /note add <text> | /note find <text>`

Return the handler output as-is.
